claim.claim-text:
1. A spinal bone plate system comprising:
an elongate plate member;
a plurality of throughbores of the plate member each extending along a respective bore axis through the plate member;
a plurality of bone anchor members each having a non-threaded head end for driving the bone anchor members into spinal bones and a threaded shank depending from the head end with the non-threaded head end being radially enlarged relative to the threaded shank;
at least one rigid pivot base for being received in one of the throughbores and having a rigid non-threaded wall and a through opening about which the non-threaded rigid wall extends and which is configured to receive one of the bone anchor members extending therethrough with the non-threaded radially enlarged head end of the one bone anchor member seated against the non-threaded rigid wall in the through opening in non-threaded engagement therewith so that the non-threaded rigid wall extends about the head end and between the head end and the plate member to completely space the head end from the plate member;
a through aperture in the wall of the pivot base extending laterally therethrough and aligned with the head end of the bone anchor when the head end is seated within the through opening of the pivot base;
at least one pivot member extending in the through aperture of the pivot base wall such that the seated bone anchor head end blocks laterally inward movement of the at least one pivot member, the at least one pivot member extending between the pivot base and the plate member to pivotally mount the pivot base to the plate member for pivoting relative thereto to allow pivoting of the rigid pivot base and the associated bone anchor member relative to the plate member with the head end of the bone anchor member seated in the pivot base opening and the bone anchor member driven into a spinal bone;
floor portions of the elongate plate member that extend laterally transverse to the bore axis inwardly into the one throughbore on either side thereof to define a narrow section of the throughbore;
lower surface portions of the rigid pivot base configured for being supported on the inwardly extending floor portions of the plate member upon pivoting of the rigid pivot base in the one throughbore; and
an inner side wall portion of the plate member extending along the throughbore adjacent to the through aperture of the pivot base wall such that the inner side wall portion blocks laterally outward movement of the pivot member.

13. A spinal bone plate system comprising:
an elongate bone plate member extending along a longitudinal axis thereof, the bone plate member having upper and lower surfaces;
a plurality of throughbores of the bone plate member extending between the upper and lower surfaces of the bone plate member and each having a pair of opposite longitudinal sides;
a plurality of bone anchor members each having a head end for driving the bone anchor member into spinal bone;
a rigid base member separate and distinct from the bone plate member for being received in one of the throughbores of the separate and distinct bone plate member;
a rigid body of the rigid base member having an opening therethrough configured to receive one of the bone anchor members extending therethrough with the head end of the bone anchor member seated in the opening, the rigid body not deforming as the head end of the bone anchor member is seated in the rigid body opening;
an upper wide portion of the base member that includes a pair of longitudinal side wall portions of the base member extending along the opposite longitudinal sides of the one throughbore which generally define a width of the base member therebetween transverse to the longitudinal axis of the bone plate member;
a lower narrower portion of the base member that is disposed under the upper wide portion so that the upper wide portion has a pair of opposite side overhang portions including the longitudinal side wall portions that extend beyond corresponding sides of the lower narrower portion;
a pair of floor portions of the bone plate member extending inwardly into the one throughbore and along the opposite longitudinal sides of the one throughbore below the upper surface of the bone plate member to define a narrow section of the one throughbore that is narrower than the width of the base member such that the floor portions support the base member received in the throughbore and allow for controlled relative motion between the base member and the bone plate member on the floor portions thereof after the bone anchor member is driven into a spinal bone and the head end is seated in the opening formed in the rigid body of the base member;
a top surface portion of the rigid body of the base member extending about the opening thereof and about the head end of the bone anchor member when the head end is seated in the opening of the rigid body;
lower surface portions of the side overhang portions of the base member disposed below the top surface portion that are configured to be supported by the inwardly extending floor portions of the bone plate member;
an upper enlarged portion of the one throughbore that opens to the upper surface of the bone plate member to form a wide section of the one throughbore across the longitudinal sides thereof that is wider than the rigid base member width to allow the rigid base member to be inserted downwardly into the throughbore upper enlarged portion with the side wall portions of the rigid base member in clearance with the opposite longitudinal sides of the throughbore in the wide section thereof;
a pin for extending between the base member and the plate member and pivotally connecting the base member to the plate member in the one throughbore;
a wall of the base member body extending about the opening;
a through aperture in the wall of the base member extending laterally therethrough and aligned with the head end of the one bone anchor member when the head portion is seated in the opening such that the seated bone anchor member head end blocks laterally inward movement of the pin; and
an inner side wall portion of the bone plate member extending along the one throughbore adjacent to the through aperture of the base member such that the side wall portion blocks laterally outward movement of the pin.

21. A spinal bone plate system comprising:
an elongate bone plate member extending along an axis thereof;
a plurality of throughbores of the bone plate member, at least one of the throughbores being axially elongated;
a plurality of bone anchor members each having a non-threaded head end for driving the bone anchor member into spinal bone and a threaded shank depending from the head end with the head end being radially enlarged relative to the shank;
a pivot base for being received in the one axially elongated throughbore;
floor portions of the plate member extending inwardly into the one throughbore along opposite sides of the throughbore to define a narrow section of the throughbore, the floor portions being configured to support the pivot base in the throughbore;
lower surface portions of the pivot base configured for being supported on the floor portions of the plate member upon pivoting of the pivot base in the one throughbore;
an opening of the pivot base configured to receive one of the bone anchor members extending therethrough with the head end thereof being seated in the opening of the pivot base;
a non-threaded wall of the pivot base extending about the opening thereof which the non-threaded head end of the one bone anchor engages as the head end is seated in the opening of the pivot base, the non-threaded pivot base wall being configured so that the wall extends about the head end of the bone anchor member and between the head end and the bone plate member to completely space the head end from the bone plate member with the head end seated in the opening of the pivot base;
a through aperture in the wall of the pivot base extending laterally therethrough and aligned with the head end of the bone anchor member when the head end is seated in the opening of the pivot base;
a pin extending in the through aperture of the pivot base wall such that the seated bone anchor head end blocks laterally inward movement of the pin;
an inner side wall portion of the plate member extending along the throughbore adjacent to the through aperture of the pivot base wall such that the side wall portion blocks laterally outward movement of the pin; and
cooperating surfaces of the one throughbore and the pivot base that allow for both translation and pivoting of the pivot base relative to the bone plate member with the bone anchor member driven into spinal bone and the head end of the bone anchor member seated in the pivot base opening.

27. A spinal bone plate system comprising:
an elongate bone plate member extending along an axis thereof;
a plurality of throughbores of the bone plate member with at least one of the throughbores having substantially straight, axially extending surfaces;
a plurality of bone anchor members each having a head end for driving the bone anchor member into spinal bone;
a rigid base member separate from the bone plate member for being received in one of the throughbores and having a rigid wall and a through opening about which the rigid wall extends and which is configured to receive one of the bone anchor members extending therethrough with the head end of the one bone anchor member seated against the rigid wall in the opening in the base member so that the rigid wall extends about the head end and between the head end and the bone plate member to completely space the head end from the bone plate member;
opposite, straight sides of the base member in confronting relation with the substantially straight, axially extending surfaces of the throughbore to keep the base member and the bone anchor member head end seated therein from turning in the one throughbore due to torque applied to the base member via the seated head end of the bone anchor member;
a through aperture in the wall of the base member extending laterally therethrough, the through aperture being aligned with the head end of the bone anchor when the head end is seated within the through opening of the base member;
a pivot member extending in the through aperture of the base member wall such that the seated bone anchor head end blocks laterally inward movement of the pivot member, the pivot member extending outwardly beyond one of the straight sides of the base member between the base member and the bone plate member to pivotally mount the base member to the plate member for pivoting relative thereto to allow pivoting of the base member and the one bone anchor member relative to the plate member with the head end of the one bone anchor member seated in the base member opening and the bone anchor member driven into a spinal bone;
floor portions of the bone plate member extending inwardly into the throughbore along the substantially straight, axially extending surfaces of the throughbore to define a narrow section of the throughbore;
lower surface portions of the base member for being supported on the inwardly extending floor portions of the plate member;
a portion of the pivot member being pivotally supported by one of the floor portions of the bone plate member for pivoting of the base member in the throughbore; and
an inner side wall portion of the plate member extending along the throughbore adjacent to the through aperture of the base member wall such that the side wall portion blocks laterally outward movement of the pivot member.

36. A bone plate system comprising:
a plate member;
at least one throughbore disposed within the plate member;
at least one bone anchor having a head portion and a shank portion, the head portion configured for driving the bone anchor shank portion into bone;
a base member separate from the plate member configured to be disposed within the throughbore, the base member having upper and lower surfaces and a through opening extending between the upper and lower surfaces sized and configured to receive the bone anchor shank portion extending therethough and to receive the bone anchor head portion seated therein;
a pin extending between the base member and the plate member which pivotally connects the base member to the plate member in the throughbore thereof so that the base member is pivotal relative to the plate member with the head portion of the bone anchor seated within the through opening of the base member;
a wall of the base member extending about the through opening;
a through aperture in the wall of the base member disposed between the upper and lower surfaces of the base member extending outward from the through opening of the base member through the base member wall to an outer surface thereof so that the through aperture has end openings that open to both the base member through opening and the base member outer surface for receiving the pin extending between the base member and the plate member, the through aperture being aligned with the head portion of the bone anchor when the head portion is seated within the through opening such that the seated bone anchor head portion blocks inward movement of the pin;
floor portions of the plate member extending inwardly into the throughbore along opposite sides of the throughbore to define a narrow section of the throughbore;
lower surface portions of the base member configured for being supported on the inwardly extending floor portions of the plate member upon pivoting of the base member in the throughbore; and
an inner side wall portion of the bone plate extending along the throughbore adjacent to the through aperture of the base member wall such that the side wall portion blocks outward movement of the pin.
